Add a Global Filter Panel Widget to Filter Data from the Dashboard

The panel can contain single or multiple global filters. Use a global filter to apply the same filter to multiple queries in the dashboard.

Each global filter must be based on a single measure, dimension, or date field. If multiple datasets are linked using a data source connection, only one of the common fields used in the connection can be included in a global filter.

Global filters can’t be used in interactions. Instead, use a single filter widget in an interaction to filter data in another dataset.

To add a global filter to the panel:

* Drag the global filter panel widget to the dashboard canvas.
* In the global filter panel widget, click .
* Select a dataset field and click Create.
* To use a different dataset, click Change Dataset.
* Select the filter operator and field values.
* These filters apply when a user opens the dashboard.

To prevent users viewing the dashboard from changing the global filter, select Locked. This option also ensures that incoming filters passed from a linked dashboard don’t override the global filter.

To limit the global filter’s picklist values based on selections in other global filters, select Dependent.

Click Apply to add the global filter to the panel.

To edit or delete a global filter, access the global filter panel by clicking the  icon at the top of the dashboard.
title: Adding Global Filters in CRM Analytics Dashboards
